<item>
            <title>[LANG-437] Complaints that the IE fix for StringEscapeUtils.escapeJavaScript is causing problems elsewhere. Rollback?</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LANG-437</link>
                <project id="12310481" key="LANG">Commons Lang</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Need to decide if we should roll &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LANG-363&quot; title=&quot;StringEscapeUtils.escapeJavaScript() method did not escape &amp;#39;/&amp;#39; into &amp;#39;\/&amp;#39;, it will make IE render page uncorrectly&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LANG-363&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LANG-363&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; back or not. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12395792">LANG-437</key>
            <summary>Complaints that the IE fix for StringEscapeUtils.escapeJavaScript is causing problems elsewhere. Rollback?</summary>
