                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12633917" author="bob fields" created="Tue, 23 Sep 2008 21:38:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This change broke our application www.andromda.org. We use StringEscapeUtils to fix documentation contained in Strings for inclusion in Java files and then compile those java files, resulting in the error:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Invalid escape sequence (valid ones are  \b  \t  \n  \f  \r  \&quot;  \&apos;  &lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt; )&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that \/ is not a valid String escape sequence.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should use escapeJavaScript if String is meant to be used in html or XML environment rather than in a Java environment.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See also &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LANG-421&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LANG-421&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12635206" author="bayard" created="Sun, 28 Sep 2008 03:35:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Does &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LANG-421&quot; title=&quot;StringEscapeUtils.escapeJava(String) escapes &amp;#39;/&amp;#39; characters&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LANG-421&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LANG-421&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; not fix this for you?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12710265" author="bayard" created="Mon, 18 May 2009 04:04:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Problems are because the escapeJavaScript change leaked into escapeJava due to shared code. Fixed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LANG-421&quot; title=&quot;StringEscapeUtils.escapeJava(String) escapes &amp;#39;/&amp;#39; characters&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LANG-421&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LANG-421&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
